SKILL|segment-anything-model|"SAM: zero-shot image segmentation via points, boxes, masks."
STEP|1|Use SAM when:**
STEP|2|Need to segment any object in images without task-specific training
STEP|3|Building interactive annotation tools with point/box prompts
STEP|4|Generating training data for other vision models
STEP|5|Need zero-shot transfer to new image domains
STEP|6|Building object detection/segmentation pipelines
STEP|7|Processing medical, satellite, or domain-specific images
STEP|8|Key features:**
STEP|9|**Zero-shot segmentation**: Works on any image domain without fine-tuning
STEP|10|**Flexible prompts**: Points, bounding boxes, or previous masks
STEP|11|**Automatic segmentation**: Generate all object masks automatically
STEP|12|**High quality**: Trained on 1.1 billion masks from 11 million images
STEP|13|**Multiple model sizes**: ViT-B (fastest), ViT-L, ViT-H (most accurate)
STEP|14|**ONNX export**: Deploy in browsers and edge devices
STEP|15|Use alternatives instead:**
STEP|16|**YOLO/Detectron2**: For real-time object detection with classes
STEP|17|**Mask2Former**: For semantic/panoptic segmentation with categories
STEP|18|**GroundingDINO + SAM**: For text-prompted segmentation
STEP|19|**SAM 2**: For video segmentation tasks
STEP|20|**[Advanced Usage](references/advanced-usage.md)** - Batching, fine-tuning, integration
STEP|21|**[Troubleshooting](references/troubleshooting.md)** - Common issues and solutions
STEP|22|**GitHub**: https://github.com/facebookresearch/segment-anything
STEP|23|**Paper**: https://arxiv.org/abs/2304.02643
STEP|24|**Demo**: https://segment-anything.com
STEP|25|**SAM 2 (Video)**: https://github.com/facebookresearch/segment-anything-2
STEP|26|**HuggingFace**: https://huggingface.co/facebook/sam-vit-huge
